Week 1:
Tasks for the week: 
    - Set up the ACTS framework on the local machine
Steps/ Tutorials:
    - Docker pull and build the image (https://github.com/acts-project/machines/pkgs/container/ubuntu2004)
    - docker pull ghcr.io/acts-project/ubuntu2004:v9
    - docker run --name [name] -v /home/<USERNAME>:/acts-project --interactive --tty ghcr.io/acts-project/ubuntu2004:v9 /bin/bash
    - docker run --name [name] -v /home/<USERNAME>:/acts-project -it ghcr.io/acts-project/ubuntu2004:v9
Build the revised version of the ACTS (https://github.com/hrzhao76/acts/tree/Add_Truth_and_Reco_Writer) (https://acts.readthedocs.io/en/latest/getting_started.html)
    - apt install wget (install wget)
    - wget [link] (get the acts zip file in the terminal)
    - apt install unzip
    - unzip [file name] (unzip the zip file)
    - mkdir [build directory name] (create a build directory)
    - cmake -B [build directory name] -S [source directory name] -DACTS_BUILD_FATRAS=ON -DACTS_BUILD_EXAMPLES=ON -DACTS_BUILD_EXAMPLES_PYTHIA8=ON
    - cd [build directory name]
    - make -j4
(Perhaps start generating a small number of events)
# ttbar event generation
    - ./ActsExamplePythia8  --rnd-seed=42 --events=3  --output-dir=data/gen/ttbar_mu10 --output-root --output-csv --gen-cms-energy-gev=14000 --gen-hard-process=Top:qqbar2ttbar=on --gen-npileup=10 -l 1 | tee log.ActsExamplePythia
